comment:
* Information about a process an app may run.  This corresponds to information collected from the
 * AndroidManifest.xml's <permission-group> tags.
 * @hide

variables.name: name
variables.comment: * The name of the process, fully-qualified based on the app's package name.

variables.name: deniedPermissions
variables.comment: * If non-null, these are permissions that are not allowed in this process.

variables.name: gwpAsanMode
variables.comment: * Indicates if the process has requested GWP-ASan to be enabled, disabled, or left unspecified.

variables.name: memtagMode
variables.comment:
* Indicates if the process has requested Memtag to be enabled (in sync or async mode),
     * disabled, or left unspecified.

variables.name: nativeHeapZeroInitialized
variables.comment: * Enable automatic zero-initialization of native heap memory allocations.

variables.name: useEmbeddedDex
variables.comment:
* Enable use of embedded dex in the APK, rather than extracted or locally compiled variants.
     * If false (default), the parent app's configuration determines behavior.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
